# Prompts & AI Integration

## Prompt Rules
- Every prompt must begin with `SYSTEM_PERSONA` and end with `JSON_MANDATE`.
- Persona: "highly intelligent email assistant" — not PM-specific.
- All model responses must be JSON. Parse with `parseJsonResponse()`.
- Always pass `currentUser` context when available.

## Background.js
- All Ollama calls happen here, never in content scripts.
- Models configured in the `MODELS` object at the top of the file.
- Use `handleXxx` pattern for message handlers.
- Always include error handling with fallback for non-JSON responses.

## Storage Keys
- Your Brain data uses `your_brain_*` prefix in `chrome.storage.local`.
- Functions: `getYourBrainExamples`, `isYourBrainEnabled`, `setYourBrainEnabled`.

## Eval Framework Sync
When changing prompt builder signatures, thread data shapes, or AI parsing logic, **always update `eval/` in the same changeset**:
- `eval/fixtures.json` — fixture `metadata`, `structuredThread`, and `expected` fields must match current prompt builder signatures.
- `eval/runner.js` — `OPERATIONS` object maps fixtures to prompt builders; update if signatures change.
- `eval/scorer.js` — scoring rubrics; update if new quality dimensions are introduced.
